               <interp inst="t18430227-969" type="date" value="18430227"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18430227-969-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-969-18430227 t18430227-969-offence-1 t18430227-969-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>969. <persName id="def1-969-18430227" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-969-18430227" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-969-18430227" type="age" value="17"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-969-18430227" type="surname" value="SHAW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-969-18430227" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM SHAW</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18430227-969-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430227-969-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430227-969-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp> for uttering counterfeit coin.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. BODKIN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">LUCAS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-811" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-811" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-811" type="surname" value="GROVE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-811" type="given" value="REBECCA"></interp>REBECCA GROVE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of John Dove Grove, a licensed victualler, who lives in Broad-street, St. Giles. On the 29th of Jan., in the afternoon, the prisoner came for a pennyworth of gin—I served him, and he gave me a bad sixpence—I bent it, and gave it to my husband—the prisoner then showed me a good sixpence—I asked if he would pay for it out of that; he said no, he would not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What did you do with the bad six<lb></lb>pence? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> My husband broke it in two and gave it to the policeman—I had not laid it down anywhere.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-812" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-812" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-812" type="surname" value="GROVE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-812" type="given" value="JOHN DOVE"></interp>JOHN DOVE GROVE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the husband of Rebecca Grove. I saw the prisoner in my house—I accused him of having given a bad sixpence—he said that was not the sixpence he gave her; that she had put that into the till and rung the changes with him—I sent for a constable, marked the bad sixpence, and gave it him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-813" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-813" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-813" type="surname" value="BARRETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-813" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BARRETT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable F</hi> 87.) On the 29th of Jan. I took the prisoner—I found on him a good sixpence—Mr. Grove delivered this bad sixpence to me—the prisoner was taken to the police office, and discharged the next day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> The whole of the case was stated? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; I have kept this bad sixpence ever since.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-814" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-814" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-814" type="surname" value="MOTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-814" type="given" value="MARIA EVELING"></interp>MARIA EVELING MOTT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. Taylor, who lives in the Arcade, Hungerford-market. On the 4th of Feb. the prisoner came in the even<lb></lb>ing for a penny bun, and gave me a bad sixpence—I looked at it and bit it—</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184302270167"></xptr>
               <p>he said it was a good one—I said I did not think it was—I gate it to my master—I went for a policeman, and when I came back the prisoner was gone.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-815" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-815" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-815" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-815" type="given" value="WILLIAM HAYWARD"></interp>WILLIAM HAYWARD TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am Mott's master—on the 4th of Feb. she gave me a bad sixpence—the prisoner asked me to take for the bun out of a good sixpence—I refused, and sent for a policeman—one came before Mott returned, and I gave the sixpence and the prisoner to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-816" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-816" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-816" type="surname" value="BOYCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-816" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BOYCE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant F</hi> 17.) On the 4th of Feb. I took the prisoner, and Mr. Taylor gave me this sixpence—I found a good sixpence on the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-817" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-817" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-817" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-817" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>MR. JOHN FIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Mint—these sixpences are both counterfeit.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
